	* [r13101] x-compile.sh:
	  
	  Kindle Hacks:
	  * X-TC:
	  * Fix a number of stuff trying to pull the strict c99 version of
	  sscanf, which we can't use w/ the K3 TC, since that's a glibc 2.7
	  feature, and we target glibc 2.5...
	  No idea why some of these seemingly cropped up recently, and how long
	  it's been broken...
	  Because, most importantly, this broke both dropbear AND OpenSSL
	  (meaning OpenSSH). :?
	  * Also mention that readelf is broken on the K3 while we're there
	  (requires qsort_r, introduced in glibc 2.8...)

