2015-02-25 04:35  NiLuJe

	* [r11654] x-compile.sh:
	  
	  Kindle Hacks:
	  * X-TC:
	  * More Python cross-compile fun...
	  Explicitly ask the linker to look for libs into its sysroot,
	  so that the spurious -L/usr/lib{,64} added add the end for some stupid
	  reason doesn't screw us up when the linker is looking fro the libc...
	  Without that, it finds the host's static libc first, which isn't as
	  gracefully
	  handled as when it finds the host's dynamic libc, which it properly
	  skips...

2015-02-25 04:11  NiLuJe

	* [r11653] x-compile.sh:
	  
	  Kindle Hacks:
	  * X-TC:
	  * Cross-compiling Python is still a bundle of fun...

2015-02-25 02:57  NiLuJe

