2011-02-28 15:41  NiLuJe

	* [r7316] freetype-git-autohint-fallback.patch[ADD], x-compile:
	  
	  Kindle Hacks:
	  * Fonts:
	  * Rebuild FreeType with commit
	  ff8095077ce454246edb93c5bc672edb2b2c8f25 reverted.
	  It's supposed to make FT fallback to autohint if the font doesn't
	  contain any bytecode
	  instructions, but on my Kindle, I'm seeing fonts *with* bytecode instr
	  triggering this fallback.
	  That effectively breaks the 'bci' setting, so revert this for now.
	  * X-TC:
	  * Revert commit ff8095077ce454246edb93c5bc672edb2b2c8f25 for FreeType

2011-02-27 19:18  NiLuJe

