	* [r7146] x-compile:
	  
	  Kindle Hacks:
	  * Fonts:
	  * Go back to a slightly more statically compiled fc-scan binary.
	  Apparently, there really is a weird ABI mimsatch causing semi-random
	  segfaults.
	  * Fix fontconfig config file generation to properly avoid multiple
	  entries for the
	  same family.
	  (Using sort was a bad idea, because, well, it sorts. And we don't want
	  that)

2010-11-11 00:17  NiLuJe

	* [r7145] x-compile:
	  
	  Kindle Hacks:
	  * Fonts:
	  * Make sure fontconfig's cache directory exists before
	  trying to create our own custom cache, because if it's not,
	  our test craps out, and fc-cache would create its cache
	  in ~/.fontconfig, which isn't what we want.

